text: Been eating at the stall more than 30 years ago.  The traditional soya sauce fried bee hoon taste remain till now.  Queue is typically long particularly on weekend morning.

Saw a queue here early morning and decided to join in! The bee hoon is really flavorful! Price is good too, beehoon + zai er + fried egg cost only $2.70. Would have been perfect if there was a vege dish (cabbage or anything) but I didn‚Äôt see it on the menu. Otherwise, super value for money!
Perfectly fried eggs, basic fried bee hoon with a plethora of fried stuff. Sinful but awesome. Slightly pricier than other stalls but well worth the calories once a week.

Friendly and speedy service, despite the long line. Both beehoon and noodle have an old school taste üëç. Price is reasonable. Aunty is generous with chilli sauce when requested, don't make faces. She is also patient and cheerful, a great way to start my day.

2 November 2022, Wednesday.
#01-158

This an old school stall, selling only fried Beehoon and noodle with some fried stuffs like, eggs, fish cake, fish fillets, chinese sausages.

It has been around since the 80s, stall owner is very fast with her service which is a important in hawker trade.

However, this stall don't open daily, open as and when she likes. üòÖ
There are time it was closed for a long duration.

Quality of her food is consistently good! Hence you can see a long queue when stall is open.

Do take note, stall is open for breakfast only. In the afternoon, the stall sells Rojak.
